Sugarloaf Mountain Park first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Sugarloaf Saw Mill had a population of 14, of which 12 were [[Non-Hispanic whites|Non-Hispanic White]] and 2 were [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]]. The median age was 57.5{{nbsp}}years.<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Sugarloaf Saw Mill CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0675592 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

There were 57 housing units at an average density of {{convert|587.6|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 9 were occupied, all by homeowners, and 48 were used seasonally.<ref name=DP1/>

